HEADWORD: gamey
<hw>gamey</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>suggestive of sexual
impropriety; <as>as, he skips asterisks and gives you the <ex>gamey</ex>
details</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> blue, gamy, juicy, naughty, racy, risque, spicy,
sexy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>foul-smelling; -- used of the smell of game
beginning to taint.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gamy, high.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>spirited and resolute.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> game, gamy, gritty, mettlesome, spirited,
spunky.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>willing to proceed or act.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> game.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gamic</ent>⟦br⟧
